wiki.summary: “See U Later” is the fourth and final track from BLACKPINK’s first EP: SQUARE UP. This track combines Pop and Hip-Hop. It is produced by Teddy Park, R.Tee, and 24, and written by Teddy Park. The intro starts with a guitar sound which makes the listeners reminiscent, while the distorted 808 bass that comes in along adds depth to the message ‘Leave because you’re a man like that’. The large space and clear drum sounds of the track also adds strength to the lyrics along with unexpected arrangement that pops out every section. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “See U Later” is the fourth and final track from BLACKPINK’s first EP: SQUARE UP. This track combines Pop and Hip-Hop. It is produced by Teddy Park, R.Tee, and 24, and written by Teddy Park. The intro starts with a guitar sound which makes the listeners reminiscent, while the distorted 808 bass that comes in along adds depth to the message ‘Leave because you’re a man like that’. The large space and clear drum sounds of the track also adds strength to the lyrics along with unexpected arrangement that pops out every section. The harmony between oriental synth-lines and the chord behind the main melody makes BLACKPINK feel like blond queens. Billboard wrote: “See U Later” is a cutting breakup track with a playful vibe that weaves between numerous genres, with ‘00s-laced dance-pop leading into the dramatic, trap-laden chorus, and a hypnotizing, horns-laced breakdown."
